<div class="container">
    <h1>🔒 PhantomLock — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="subhead">
        Next-Gen Privacy Vault · Stealth Mode · Encrypted Vault & Secure Chat
    </div>
    <div class="last-updated">
        📅 Last updated: May 18, 2026
    </div>

    <p><strong>PhantomLock</strong> (package: <code>com.lighteast.phantomlock</code>) is developed and maintained by <strong>Esmatullah Sangary</strong> (“we”, “our”, or “us”). We prioritize your privacy and security above everything else. This Privacy Policy explains how PhantomLock handles data — and importantly, what it <strong>never</strong> collects or shares.</p>

    <p>By using PhantomLock, you agree to the practices described in this policy. Since the app is designed as a <strong>private vault, stealth security suite, and encrypted chat tool</strong>, most of your sensitive content remains exclusively on your device, encrypted with keys that never leave your Android Keystore.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>1. What Data Does PhantomLock Collect?</h2>
    <p>Because PhantomLock is a security & privacy-first application, we intentionally minimize data collection. However, to provide core functionality (including optional ads via AdMob) and app-lock features, certain limited data may be processed:</p>

    <div class="badge-list">
        <strong>✅ NO personal identifiable information (PII) is ever sold or shared for marketing.</strong><br>
        <strong>✅ NO access to your files, notes, chats, or decoy PINs.</strong><br>
        <strong>✅ All vault content (photos, documents, encrypted chats) stays 100% locally encrypted.</strong>
    </div>

    <h3>📱 Automatically Processed Data (AdMob & Analytics)</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Advertising ID (AAID / GAID):</strong> PhantomLock integrates <strong>Google AdMob</strong> to show occasional ads (e.g., in settings or after specific actions). AdMob may collect your device’s advertising identifier to serve personalized or non-personalized ads based on your preferences. You can reset or opt out of ad personalization anytime in <strong>Android Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization</strong>.</li>
        <li><strong>IP address & general device information:</strong> For ad delivery and fraud prevention, AdMob may collect IP address, device model, OS version, and app crash diagnostics. None of this is linked to your vault identity or personal files.</li>
        <li><strong>App usage & crash reports:</strong> We may receive anonymized crash reports via Google Play Console. These never include your vault PINs, encrypted content, or private keys.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>🔐 Permissions & On-Device Data (Never sent to servers)</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Camera & Media:</strong> Used only when you <em>manually</em> import files into the vault or capture intruder photos (wrong PIN attempt). All images remain encrypted on-device inside <code>/files/phantom_vault/</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Location (fine/coarse):</strong> Only accessed if you enable <strong>Intruder Detection</strong> (to log GPS when a wrong PIN is entered). Location data is stored locally inside the encrypted database (SQLCipher) and never transmitted to us or third parties.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Access / App List:</strong> Required for the <strong>App Lock</strong> feature. PhantomLock queries installed apps to let you lock specific applications. This data never leaves your phone.</li>
        <li><strong>Biometric (fingerprint/face):</strong> Used to unlock the vault. Biometric credentials are handled by Android Keystore — we never receive or store raw biometric data.</li>
        <li><strong>Audio & Bluetooth:</strong> Optional for encrypted chat (future P2P voice/offline features). No audio or Bluetooth data is collected externally.</li>
        <li><strong>Outgoing calls / Dial code:</strong> The <code>PROCESS_OUTGOING_CALLS</code> permission allows PhantomLock to detect your secret dial code (e.g., <code>*#6666#</code>) to launch the app in Ghost Mode. The app does <strong>not</strong> record calls or phone numbers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How Is Your Data Stored & Secured?</h2>
    <p>PhantomLock was built with defense-in-depth:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Local only architecture:</strong> All vault files, notes, encrypted chat messages, and intruder logs are stored inside an SQLCipher-encrypted Room database + AES-256-GCM encrypted blobs on device storage. Keys are derived from your PIN + hardware-bound Android Keystore (PBKDF2 with 310,000 iterations).</li>
        <li><strong>No cloud backup:</strong> Manifest explicitly disables Android backups (<code>allowBackup="false"</code>). Your secrets never sync to Google Drive or any cloud provider unless you explicitly export them.</li>
        <li><strong>Zero-knowledge design:</strong> The developer (<strong>Esmatullah Sangary</strong>) has no technical ability to access your files, PIN, fake vault content, or private keys. Not even remote debugging can reveal vault content.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Services (AdMob)</h2>
    <p>We use <strong>Google AdMob</strong> to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and process data as described in <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Advertising Policy</a>. Their privacy policy is available at: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>.</p>
    <p>PhantomLock does not share any vault content, contacts, or private media with AdMob or any other third party. The only data AdMob may receive is standard ad-related identifiers (Advertising ID) and device signals.</p>

    <h3>Children’s Privacy</h3>
    <p>PhantomLock is <strong>not intended for children under 13</strong> (or 16 in certain regions). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided data via AdMob identifiers, contact us to ensure deletion.</p>

    <h2>4. Intruder Detection & Decoy Mode</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Intruder photos & location:</strong> When someone enters a wrong PIN, PhantomLock may silently capture a front-camera photo (if permission granted) and record approximate location. This evidence stays inside the encrypted vault and is only visible to you. It is <strong>never</strong> transmitted to any server unless you manually share it.</li>
        <li><strong>Fake / Decoy Vault:</strong> You may set a secondary “fake PIN” that opens a decoy vault. This decoy environment contains no real data. PhantomLock does not log which PIN you use; the choice is entirely local.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Ghost Mode, Accessibility & Overlay Permissions</h2>
    <p>Ghost Mode hides the launcher icon and removes the app from recents. The <strong>Accessibility Service</strong> (AppLockAccessibilityService) intercepts app launches to show a PIN overlay when you open a locked app. We do not record any keystrokes outside the overlay, nor do we access content of other apps. Accessibility data is processed exclusively on-device to enforce lock policies you define.</p>
    <p>You can revoke Accessibility permission anytime in Android Settings → Accessibility → Installed services → PhantomLock App Lock.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
    <p>All data you store in PhantomLock (files, notes, chat messages) remains until you manually delete items or uninstall the app. Uninstalling PhantomLock will <strong>permanently delete all encrypted vault data</strong> because the encryption keys are tied to the app installation. We strongly recommend exporting important files before uninstallation.</p>
    <p>No user data is retained on external servers.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Choices & Control</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Ad personalization:</strong> Opt-out using Android’s “Opt out of Ads Personalization” setting.</li>
        <li><strong>Permissions:</strong> You can deny camera, location, storage, or usage access at any time. Core vault functions (except related features) will still work.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete all data:</strong> Uninstall the app or use “Wipe Vault” inside settings. All encrypted containers will be erased.</li>
        <li><strong>Disable App Lock:</strong> Turn off accessibility service to remove overlay functionality.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time to reflect legal requirements or feature changes. The “Last updated” date at the top will change accordingly. Material updates will be displayed inside the app (e.g., via a dialog). Continued use of PhantomLock after changes means you accept the revised policy.</p>

